-- HCL Technologies Shares Sold in $126 Million Block, Sale Document Shows
-- Ruth David
-- 2010-06-24T06:21:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-24/hcl-technologies-shares-sold-in-126-million-block-sale-document-shows.html

          
          
             HCL Technologies Ltd.  shares were
sold for 5.8 billion rupees ($126 million) in a block trade,
according to a sale document.  
 The shares were sold at 347 rupees each, according to the
document. Citigroup Inc. and Deutsche Bank AG managed the sale.  
 Debasis Ghosh , a Mumbai-based spokesman at Citigroup, and
Deutsche Bank’s Mumbai-based spokesman Linus Chettiar declined
to comment. Madhavi Anant, a spokeswoman for HCL, also declined
to immediately comment.  
 About 15.98 million shares, or 2.4 percent of HCL’s equity,
changed hands in a single block deal on the Bombay Stock
Exchange today, according to Bloomberg data.  
